.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/manual/coreutils.html#ls-k'\fB\-k, \-\-kibibytes\fP\X'tty: link'
default to 1024\-byte blocks for file system usage;
used only with \fB\-s\fR and per directory totals
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/manual/coreutils.html#ls-l'\fB\-l\fP\X'tty: link'
use a long listing format
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/manual/coreutils.html#ls-L'\fB\-L, \-\-dereference\fP\X'tty: link'
when showing file information for a symbolic link,
show information for the file the link references
rather than for the link itself
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/manual/coreutils.html#ls-m'\fB\-m\fP\X'tty: link'
fill width with a comma separated list of entries
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/manual/coreutils.html#ls-n'\fB\-n, \-\-numeric\-uid\-gid\fP\X'tty: link'
like \fB\-l\fR, but list numeric user and group IDs
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/manual/coreutils.html#ls-N'\fB\-N, \-\-literal\fP\X'tty: link'
print entry names without quoting
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/manual/coreutils.html#ls-o'\fB\-o\fP\X'tty: link'
like \fB\-l\fR, but do not list group information
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/manual/coreutils.html#ls-p'\fB\-p, \-\-indicator\-style=\,slash\fP\X'tty: link'\/\fR
append / indicator to directories
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/manual/coreutils.html#ls-q'\fB\-q, \-\-hide\-control\-chars\fP\X'tty: link'
print ? instead of nongraphic characters
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/manual/coreutils.html#ls--show-control-chars'\fB\-\-show\-control\-chars\fP\X'tty: link'
show nongraphic characters as\-is;
the default, unless program is 'ls' and output is a terminal
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/manual/coreutils.html#ls-Q'\fB\-Q, \-\-quote\-name\fP\X'tty: link'
enclose entry names in double quotes
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/manual/coreutils.html#ls--quoting-style'\fB\-\-quoting\-style=WORD\fP\X'tty: link'
use quoting style WORD for entry names:
literal, locale, shell, shell\-always,
